history.content: A similar post was uploaded a couple hours ago, and I'd like to ask for advice as well. I took 61A in the spring and am currently taking 70, so 61B will be my last class necessary to declare. However, I'm also gunning for a history minor and was thinking of taking two history classes (one upper div, one lower div) this semester as well. I will also be working 20 hours a week. Would it be feasible given this time constraint to adequately search for internships and prepare for interviews? Or would I be better off postponing a history class to spring? TIA!
